==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stooge
<hw>Stooge</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A person of
unquestioning obedience.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> flunky, flunkey, yes-man.</syn></p> <p><sn>2.</sn>
<def>A victim of ridicule or prank.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> butt, goat, laughingstock.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 3.0</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stooge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stooge
<hw>Stooge</hw>, <pos>v.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Cruise in slow or
routine flights.</def> <sn>2.</sn> <def>Act as the stooge; <p><q>"His
role was to stooge for the popular comedian."</q></p></def> <sn>2.</sn>
<def>Act as a stooge, in a compliant or subordinate manner; <p><q>"He
stooged for the flamboyant Senator."</q></p></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 3.0</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stook</ent>⟦br⟧
